sense.name: physically grapple with an opponent
sense.examples: At the circus we saw a man wrestle with an alligator. The children wrestled in the garden. He's wrestled on the school's team for the last two years. We wrestled the table through the door and up the stairs.

sense.name: fight in an abstract way with a force, idea, or opponent
sense.examples: She wrestled with her conscience. I have wrestled with these questions. We wrestled with these problems in the early days of the organization. They have wrestled the power away from the PCS in entirety. He wrestled with his collegues for years over the direction of the department.
